IN THE CATHOLIC UNIVERSITY CENTER OF THE UNIVERSITY OF 
PUERTO RICO. HIS PROCESS OF BEATIFICATION WAS ONE OF THE 
SHORTEST IN RECENT HISTORY, LASTING ONLY NINE YEARS. (NOTE: 
THE VATICAN TREATS PUERTO RICO AS A SEPARATE ECCLESIASTICAL 
JURISDICTION FROM THE UNITED STATES WITH ITS OWN BISHOPS 
CONFERENCE. THE NUNCIO IN THE DOMINICAN REPUBLIC, AMCIT 
ARCHBISHOP TIMOTHY BROGLIO ALSO ACTS AS THE PAPAL 
REPRESENTATIVE TO PUERTO RICO, BUT ONLY FOR SPECIFICALLY 
ECCLESIASTICAL MATTERS. POST FURTHER NOTES THAT AN OFFICIAL 
DELEGATION FROM THE GOVERNMENT OF THE COMMONWEALTH OF PUERTO 
RICO, HEADED BY THE SECRETARY OF STATE ATTENDED THE 
