SUBJECT: VATICAN ARCHIVES Q \"THE REAL STORY\" 
 
UP A SERIES OF HISTORICAL DOSSIERS, INCLUDING PRIMARY 
DOCUMENTS. YET HE SAID HE WAS SUSPICIOUS THAT THE COMMISSION 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  04258  02 OF 02  131206Z 
HAD NO INTENT TO THOROUGHLY EXPLORE THE QUESTIONS SINCE THEY 
ONLY ALLOCATED THREE HOURS TO THEIR ENCOUNTER.  MOREOVER, 
AFTER REVIEWING DOSSIERS ON ONLY 12 QUESTIONS, SOME OF THE 
COMMISSION MEMBERS LAUNCHED INTO POLEMICAL ATTACKS ON THE 
HOLY SEE FOR ITS ALLEGED LACK OF COOPERATION.  SOME 
COMMISSION MEMBERS LATER MADE PUBLIC STATEMENTS ABOUT A LACK 
OF SUCH ON HIS PART. GUMPEL LAMENTED THE AGGRESSIVE POSITION 
TAKEN TOWARDS HIM PERSONALLY BY SOME MEMBERS OF THE 
COMMISSION AND THE LACK OF PERSONAL AND ACADEMIC COHESION IN 
THE GROUP OF HISTORIANS AS A WHOLE.  HE HAS DEPOSITED THE 
TAPES OF THE MEETING WITH THE VATICAN.  HIGH LEVEL VATICAN 
OFFICIALS HAVE LISTENED TO THE RECORDINGS AND EXPRESSED 
REGRET AT THE UNSCHOLARLY METHODOLOGY OF SOME OF THE JEWISH 
MEMBERS. THOSE SAME VATICAN OFFICIALS, HE SAID, EXPRESSED 
APPRECIATION FOR FR. GUMPEL\'S ACUTE KNOWLEDGE OF THE 
SITUATION AND HIS SCIENTIFIC PROFESSIONALISM.  GUMPEL MADE 
IT CLEAR TO A/DCM THAT EVEN POPE JOHN PAUL II IS AWARE OF 
THE SITUATION. 
 
------------------------- 
I AM A GERMAN, NOT A NAZI 
------------------------- 
 
4. (C)  GUMPEL WAS PERSONALLY PAINED BY SOME OF THE AD 
HOMINUM COMMENTARY DIRECTED AT HIM BY JEWISH MEMBERS OF THE 
COMMISSION AND OTHER JEWISH ORGANIZATIONS.  HE STRESSED TO 
A/DCM THAT HE HAS REFRAINED FROM CHARACTERIZING THE WORK OF 
CERTAIN COMMISSION MEMBERS \"UNTIL NOW\" AS A PROFESSIONAL 
COURTESY AND OUT OF RESPECT.  HOWEVER, HE WARNED THAT IF 
ATTACKS AND FALSEHOODS CONTINUED, HE WOULD RELEASE THE TAPES 
OF THE MEETINGS. (NOTE: GUMPEL INSINUATED THAT THE RELEASE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  04258  02 OF 02  131206Z 
TO THE TAPES WOULD PROVE TO BE EMBARRASSING FOR SOME OF THE 
COMMISSION MEMBERS, DEMONSTRATING THAT THE COMMISSION ITSELF 
WAS \"IN CRISIS\" BECAUSE OF CERTAIN MEMBERS\' UNPROFESSIONAL 
BEHAVIOR.  END NOTE).  GUMPEL ALSO EXPRESSED CONCERN ABOUT 
REFERENCES IN THE MEDIA AND IN OTHER COMMENTS TO HIM AS THE 
\"GERMAN JESUIT.\"   GUMPEL TOLD A/DCM THAT HIS FAMILY HAD 
BEEN VICTIMS OF NAZI PERSECUTION AND SEVERAL HAD BEEN KILLED 
BY THE NAZIS.  HE HIMSELF HAD TO FLEE NAZI GERMANY AS A 
REFUGEE, FIRST TO FRANCE AND THEN LATER TO HOLLAND.  HE 
RECALLED THAT AT ONE POINT A REPORTER HAD PLANNED TO PRINT 
AN ASSERTION THAT GUMPEL WAS A NAZI HIMSELF -- SOMETHING 
GUMPEL SAID WAS LIBELOUS, AND WHICH HE WAS MORE THAN WILLING 
TO GO TO COURT TO FIGHT. 
 
5. (C)  GUMPEL SAID HE WAS NOT SURPRISED WHEN THE JEWISH- 
VATICAN COMMISSION DECIDED TO SUSPEND ITS WORK. HE CLAIMED 
THAT SOME OF ITS MEMBERS HAD AGENDAS THAT WENT BEYOND THE 
SCOPE OF THE COMMISSION\'S MANDATE (TO STUDY THE TWELVE 
VOLUMES).   OBJECTIONS ABOUT A LACK OF ACCESS TO THE VATICAN 
ARCHIVES OR ABOUT THE VATICAN HAVING SOMETHING TO HIDE ARE, 
IN GUMPEL\'S OPINION, A SMOKE SCREEN FOR POLITICAL AGENDAS 
WHICH HAVE LITTLE TO DO WITH THE SERIOUS HISTORICAL STUDY 
THAT IS HIS LIFE.  HE CLOSED BY SAYING THAT THE VATICAN 
WANTS TO LET PASS A PERIOD OF TIME BEFORE REOPENING THIS 
DISCUSSION.  HE SAID THAT THE VATICAN AND HE HIMSELF WERE 
MORE THAN WILLING TO DISCUSS ANY ANOMALIES OR QUESTIONS 
RELATING TO THE 12-VOLUME HISTORY ALREADY PUBLISHED.  THEY 
JUST DIDN\'T THINK THAT THE JUST-DISBANDED COMMISSION 
CONSISTED OF THE RIGHT MIX OF PEOPLE TO BE ABLE TO DO SO. 
MERANTE 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  04258  02 OF 02  131206Z 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
