TAGS: PREL, PGOV, PHUM, EAGR, KIRF, VT, Biotechnology, Human Trafficking, religious freedom 
SUBJECT: BIWEEKLY ACTIVITY REPORT FEBRUARY 15-MARCH 1 
 
REF: VATICAN 1152 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: CDA JOSEPH MERANTE, REASON 1.5 (B,D) 
 
 1.  (C)  THIS CABLE REPORTS ON EMBASSY VATICAN\'S BIWEEKLY 
ACTIVITIES FOR THE PERIOD FEBRUARY 14-MARCH 1, 2002.  IT IS 
INTENDED TO SUMMARIZE, BUT NOT EXHAUSTIVELY REPORT, OUR 
ACTIVITIES DURING THE PREVIOUS TWO WEEKS.  COVERED IN THIS 
CABLE ARE: 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  01179  061611Z 
-- TRI-MISSION BIOTECH IWG 
-- SANT\'EGIDIO DINNER IHO AMBASSADOR 
-- DCM ON TRAFFICKING CONFERENCE 
-- SECURITY ISSUES 
-- NEW VATICAN ME DIRECTOR 
-- CHINA RELIGIOUS FREEDOM 
-- CATHOLIC U IN TIRANA? 
-- VATICAN POL/MIL INITIATIVE 
-- REPORTING: PAPAL ARCHIVES, POTUS CHINA POINTS, VISA 
FACILITATION FOR WORLD YOUTH DAY. 
 
2.  (SBU)  TRI-MISSION BIOTECH IWG: POLOFF AND ASSISTANT 
ATTENDED 02/15 TRI-MISSION IWG (EMBASSY ROME, FODAG AND 
EMBASSY VATICAN) LED BY EMBASSY ROME AGCOUNS, TO DEVELOP 
APPROACH ON AGRICULTURAL BIOTECHNOLOGY ISSUES.  EMBASSY 
VATICAN WILL LOOK FOR OPPORTUNITIES (EXPERT SPEAKERS, DVC\'S 
INVITATIONAL TRAVEL, ETC.) TO CARRY THE USG MESSAGE ON 
BIOTECHNOLOGY TO VATICAN DECISION-MAKERS IN COORDINATION WITH 
THE OTHER U.S. MISSIONS IN ROME. 
 
3.  (C) SANT\'EGIDIO DINNER IHO AMBASSADOR: SANT\'EGIDIO 
FOUNDER ANDREA RICCARDI HOSTED AMBASSADOR AND EMBOFFS TO 
RECOGNIZE CLOSE COOPERATION WITH THE USG. KEY EMBASSY 
INTERLOCUTORS INCLUDED DON VICENZO PAGLIA, BALKANS EXPERT AND 
BISHOP OF TERNI, AND AFRICA HAND DON MATTEO ZUPPI. RICCARDI 
AND ZUPPI RELATED RECENT AND PAST SANT\'EGIDIO INTERACTIONS 
WITH FIDEL CASTRO. 
(SEPTEL TO FOLLOW) 
 
4.  (U) DCM ON TRAFFICKING CONFERENCE: DCM TRAVELED 02/19 TO 
FERRARA TO MEET WITH LOCAL CARITAS GROUP WHICH HAD HELD AN 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  01179  061611Z 
ANTI-TRAFFICKING CONFERENCE IN 02/01.  GAINED INSIGHTS FOR 
SIMILAR CONFERENCE EMBASSY VATICAN IS ORGANIZING FOR MAY. 
(REFTEL) 
 
5. (U) DCM HOSTED NEW DIRECTOR OF MIDDLE EAST AFFAIRS, THOMAS 
COPPOLA, FOR LUNCH.  COPPOLA\'S PORTFOLIO IS CONSIDERED TO BE 
ONE OF THE MOST SENSITIVE IN THE MINISTRY.  AS HAD FM TAURAN, 
COPPOLA SERVED AT THE NUNCIATURE IN LEBANON, AND WE SHOULD 
THEREFORE EXPECT CONTINUED ACTIVE VATICAN ENGAGEMENT WITH US 
IN THE ISSUES OF LEBANON AND SYRIA. (SEPTEL TO FOLLOW) 
 
6.  (U)  SECURITY ISSUES: PSO ATTENDED ROME EAC AND WORKED 
WITH ROME RSO TO MAINTAIN HEIGHTENED SECURITY AT CHANCERY AND 
RESIDENCE. 
 
7. (C)  CHINA RELIGIOUS FREEDOM: POLOFF MET WITH FIDES CHINA 
EXPERT FATHER BERNARDO CERVELLERA AND SEPARATELY TAIWAN 
EMBOFF TO DISCUSS VATICAN CONCERNS ON RELIGIOUS FREEDOM IN 
THE PRC. TAIWAN EMBOFF ADMITTED TAIWAN EMBASSY MAINTAINS 
DISCRETE CONTACTS WITH THE CIRCA 25 PRC SEMINARIANS SPONSORED 
BY THE VATICAN FOR CLERICAL TRAINING IN ROME (REFTEL). 
 
8.  (U) CATHOLIC U IN TIRANA?  DCM AND POLOFF WERE TOLD 02/27 
BY BALKANS DIRECTOR MARINO THAT THE GOA HAD DONATED, FOR $1, 
A LARGE PLOT OF LAND IN ALBANIA OUTSIDE TIRANA FOR THE SITE 
OF A NEW CATHOLIC UNIVERSITY.  MARINO SAID THE VATICAN 
SUPPORTS THIS PROJECT, AND THAT THE NEXT PHASE IS FOR THE 
TIRANA DIOCESE TO ORGANIZE AN ENDOWMENT FOR FUNDING 
CONSTRUCTION AND OPERATIONS.  THE HOLY SEE ITSELF WOULD ONLY 
PROVIDE VERY LIMITED RESOURCES IN THAT REGARD.  HE INQUIRED 
WHETHER PD/ECA HAD ANY PROGRAMS TO SUPPORT UNIVERSITY 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  01179  061611Z 
DEVELOPMENT IN THE BALKANS OR THE DEVELOPING WORLD. 
 
9. (U) VATICAN POL/MIL INITIATIVE: AMBASSADOR MET WITH 
EMBASSY ROME DATTS TO MAP OUT STRATEGY FOR INCREASED VATICAN 
EXPOSURE TO CINSCOC.  AMBASSADOR PLANS APRIL 10 GATHERING 
AROUND PRESENTATION OF U.S. ARTIST\'S PAINTING TO POPE, TO PUT 
BROAD SAMPLE OF VATICAN FOREIGN MINISTRY OFFICIALS IN CONTACT 
WITH CINCSOC AND OTHER U.S. MEDITERRANEAN-BASED MILITARY 
OFFICERS. 
 
10. (C) REPORTING: VATICAN 8819: VATICAN PARTIALLY OPENS WW 
II PAPAL ARCHIVES; VATICAN 826: FM TAURAN RAISES CHINA POINTS 
FOR POTUS\' TRIP;  VATICAN 1036: VATICAN SEEKS VISA 
FACILITATION FOR WORLD YOUTH DAY ATTENDEES. MERANTE 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
