SUBJECT: DEMARCHE ON UNGA SPECIAL SESSION ON CHILDREN 
 
REF: STATE 71201 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: AMBASSADOR JIM NICHOSON, REASON E.O. 12958 1.5 (B,D). 
 
1. (C)  AMBASSADOR, MEETING ON POST\'S UPCOMING 
ANTI-TRAFFICKING CONFERENCE WITH VATICAN DFM MIGLIORE AND U/S 
OF THE PONTIFICAL COUNCIL FOR JUSTICE AND PEACE, MONS. FRANK 
DEWANE, DELIVERED REFTEL POINTS. BOTH MIGLIORE AND DEWANE 
UNDERSTOOD THE ISSUES RIGHT AWAY AND EXPRESSED A WILLINGNESS 
TO RESPOND TO THE USG REQUEST IN THE LEAD-UP TO THE SPECIAL 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  01920  180556Z 
SESSION.  (NOTE: JUSTICE AND PEACE TYPICALLY STAFFS THE 
VATICAN\'S DELEGATIONS TO UN SPECIAL SESSIONS TOGETHER WITH 
THEIR PERMREP). 
 
2.  (C)  MIGLIORE SAID THAT THE HOLY SEE HAD ALREADY SPOKEN 
TO TWO OR THREE LATIN AMERICAN GOVERNMENTS ON THE LIST OF 
THOSE PROVIDED REFTEL, AND UNDERTOOK TO DO MORE.  HE FURTHER 
WELCOMED OUR REQUEST TO MEET NEXT WEEK TO SEE HOW ANY OF 
THOSE CAPITALS MIGHT HAVE RESPONDED.  POST WILL REPORT BACK 
NLT END OF NEXT WEEK WITH THIS FOLLOW-UP. 
NICHOLSON 
 
