MALFEASANCE AND CORRUPTION.  TAURAN WAS RECEPTIVE, AND 
APPEARED WILLING TO DO  MORE TO PRESSURE BISHOP PERIC OF 
MOSTAR AND THE MOSTAR FRANCISCANS TO DESIST FROM POLITICAL 
SUPPORT FOR HARD-LINE HDZ NATIONALIST POSITIONS. (NOTE: 
BEECROFT\'S ASSISTANT TOLD POLOFF THE NEXT MORNING THAT A 
03/26 MEETING WITH THE HEAD OF THE FRANCISCAN ORDER HAD GONE 
WELL; THE FRANCISCANS SAID THEY HAD REPLACED THE SUPERIOR 
GENERAL OF THE BOSNIAN FRANCISCANS WITH A CROAT-AMERICAN, WHO 
PRESUMABLY WOULD BE LESS TOLERANT OF FRANCISCAN SHENANIGANS 
IN BOSNIA). 
 
