ROTA-GRAZIOZI TO DISCUSS 3/19 VATICAN VISIT OF TAIWAN VICE 
PRESIDENT ANNETTE HSIU-LIEN LU. DUE TO THE VATICAN\'S OFFICIAL 
CLOSURE 3/19 FOR ST. JOSEPH\'S DAY, VATICAN FM TAURAN RECEIVED 
LU IN HIS PRIVATE QUARTERS.  ROTA-GRAZIOZI STATED THE MEETING 
WAS WITHOUT SUBSTANCE, A PROTOCOL STOP IN AN ITINERARY THAT 
INCLUDED THE VATICAN MUSEUMS AND ST. PETER\'S BASILICA. 
 
7. (C) EASTER CEREMONIES:  AMBASSADOR AND EMBASSY OFFICERS 
ATTENDED THE WEEKLONG SERIES OF OFFICIAL VATICAN EASTER 
CEREMONIES, TAKING ADVANTAGE OF SIGNIFICANT TIME IN THE 
PRESENCE OF THE POPE TO ASSESS HIS PHYSICAL WELLBEING.  HE 
SEEMS TO BE OK. (SEE REFTEL) 
 
8.  (U) TIP CONFERENCE: DURING MARCH EMBASSY MADE PROGRESS IN 
ORGANIZING THE MAY 15-16 CONFERENCE ON THE HUMAN RIGHT 
DIMENSION OF TIP.  WE LOCKED IN SEVERAL KEY SPEAKERS, 
INCLUDING CARDINAL SODANO AND STABILITY PACT TTIP TASK FORCE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
