E.O. 12958: DECL: 05/08/2012 
TAGS: FR, GM, IT, KNAR, PHUM, PREL, SOCI, VT 
SUBJECT: HOLOCAUST ENVOY\'S VATICAN FAREWELL CALL 
 
ENDURING CONCERNS ABOUT THE MIDDLE EAST CONFLICT. CARDINAL 
KASPAR, ON THE OTHER HAND, SEEMED MORE AT EASE WITH THE 
SUBJECT, WHICH HE VIEWS IN THE CONTEXT OF A COMMITMENT TO 
JEWISH-CHRISTIAN RECONCILIATION.  KASPAR BELIEVES THE VATICAN 
HAS TAKEN IMPORTANT AND IRREVERSIBLE STEPS FORWARD TO DEFUSE 
THE ARCHIVAL DISPUTE, YET HE IS EVIDENTLY DISAPPOINTED AT THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  02229  02 OF 02  081738Z 
PERCEIVED LACK OF RECIPROCAL GESTURES; HE APPEALED 
CONTINUALLY FOR THE NEED FOR MUTUAL TRUST IN ORDER TO ADVANCE 
FURTHER.  KASPAR, WHO BRIEFLY TAUGHT IN THE U.S. AS A GUEST 
PROFESSOR, WAS PLEASED TO LEARN MORE OF USG INITIATIVES, 
PARTICULARLY ON HOLOCAUST COMPENSATION; THE CHANCE TO 
CONVERSE IN HIS NATIVE GERMAN ALSO APPEARED TO ELICIT A MORE 
AMIABLE ATTITUDE REGARDING A TOPIC THAT GENERALLY HAS THE 
VATICAN IMMEDIATELY ON THE DEFENSIVE. 
 
8.  (U) AMBASSADOR BINDENAGEL HAS CLEARED THIS CABLE. 
NICHOLSON 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
