SUBJECT: AG-BIOTECH: GETTING THE VATICAN TO \"YES.\" 
 
7. (C) GENERALLY POSITIVE:  BISHOP ELIO SGRECCIA, VICE 
PRESIDENT, PONTIFICAL ACADEMY FOR LIFE. SGRECCIA IS THE TOP 
VATICAN ETHICIST SPECIALIZING IN BIOTECHNOLOGY, MEDICAL 
ETHICS, HEALTH AND FAMILY ISSUES. HIS APPROACH TO 
BIOTECHNOLOGY IS ONE OF CAUTIOUS OPTIMISM - THE THEORETICAL 
BENEFITS NEED TO BE BALANCED BY ADEQUATE RESEARCH AND PATIENT 
OBSERVATION. LIKE ALL VATICAN OFFICIALS HE LOOKS TO THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  02268  02 OF 03  100540Z 
SECRETARIAT OF STATE FOR GUIDANCE AND PERMISSION TO UNDERTAKE 
 
SIPDIS 
BIOTECHNOLOGY INITIATIVES. THE ACADEMY FOR LIFE HAS PUBLISHED 
THE VATICAN\'S CLEAREST POSITION TO DATE ON BIOTECHNOLOGY. 
SGRECCIA WAS EXTREMELY SUPPORTIVE OF AN EMBASSY INITIATIVE 
THAT BROUGHT U.S. BIOTECHNOLOGIST, C.S. PRAKASH, AND VATICAN 
SCIENTISTS TOGETHER FOR A ROUND TABLE IN 2001.  AT A RECENT 
LUNCH, SGRECCIA TOLD DCM THAT HE LOOKED FORWARD TO WORKING 
WITH US ON THIS ISSUE. 
 
8. (C)  GENERALLY NEGATIVE:  ARCHBISHOP AGOSTINO MARCHETTO, 
PERMANENT OBSERVER, FAO, ROME, AND SINCE NOVEMBER 2001 
SECRETARY OF THE PONTIFICAL COUNCIL FOR THE PASTORAL CARE OF 
 
SIPDIS 
MIGRANTS AND ITINERANTS. HE ENTERED THE HOLY SEE DIPLOMATIC 
SERVICE IN 1968, AND SERVED IN A NUMBER OF SUB-SAHARAN 
NUNCIATURES. MARCHETTO IS THE CLASSIC EUROPEAN BIOTECHNOLOGY 
SKEPTIC. HIS POSITION APPEARS BASED MORE ON POPULAR 
PERCEPTIONS OF GMOS THAN ON GOOD SCIENCE. HE RELISHES PLAYING 
THE DEVIL\'S ADVOCATE AND CONCENTRATING ON THE \"WHAT IFS.\" 
YET, LIKE THE REST OF THE HOLY SEE, HIS PRIMARY MOTIVATION IS 
SERVING HUMANITY.  IF HE CAN BE PERSUADED THAT GMOS PRESENT A 
NET BENEFIT, HE WOULD BE A POWERFUL ADVOCATE FOR THEM. 
 
9.  (C)  GENERALLY POSITIVE:  ARCHBISHOP DIARMUID MARTIN, 
PERMANENT OBSERVER, UN OFFICES AND SPECIALIST AGENCIES, 
GENEVA. MARTIN, A FORMER IV VISITOR, IS NOT A PROFESSIONALLY 
TRAINED VATICAN DIPLOMAT AND THUS UNTAINTED BY THE PALL OF 
\"SUPER CAUTION.\" HE CALLS A SPADE A SPADE AND APPRECIATES 
GOOD SCIENCE. HE WOULD BE AN IMPORTANT ALLY ON THE BIOTECH 
INTERNATIONAL PLAYING FIELD. HIS REPUTATION IN WORLD TRADE 
AND MONETARY CIRCLES IS HIGH, MAKING HIM POTENTIALLY 
INFLUENTIAL WITH DEVELOPING NATIONS. MARTIN\'S FOCUS ON HUMAN 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  02268  02 OF 03  100540Z 
RIGHTS ISSUES IN GENEVA COULD BE AN ENTRY POINT FOR THE 
PROMOTION OF BIOTECH BENEFITS. 
 
10.  (C)  GENERALLY POSITIVE: MONSIGNOR CELESTINO MIGLIORE, 
DEPUTY FOREIGN MINISTER. MIGLIORE WILL LIKELY BE RESPONSIBLE 
FOR GIVING THE WORKING LEVEL \"OK\" TO MOST BIOTECHNOLOGY 
INITIATIVES. AS IS MARTIN, MIGLIORE IS PRAGMATIC AND 
STRAIGHTFORWARD. ONE OF THE EMBASSY\'S MOST ACCESSIBLE 
HIGH-LEVEL INTERLOCUTORS, WE CAN EXPECT HIM TO BE REASONABLE. 
 HE HAS FIRST HAND EXPERIENCE OF THE PROBLEMS CAUSED IN 
DEVELOPING COUNTRIES BY MALNUTRITION AND CROP FAILURE. HE 
SERVED AT THE NUNCIATURE IN WASHINGTON DURING THE 1990S AND 
WOULD BE OPEN TO THE BENEFITS OF BIOTECHNOLOGY, BUT HE WOULD 
ALSO INSIST ON ADEQUATE PRECAUTIONS BEFORE GIVING HIS \"NULLA 
OSTA\". (NOTE: IT IS CLASSIC VATICAN STRATEGY TO NOT MAKE A 
MOVE BEFORE RECEIVING PERMISSION -- THE \"NULLA OSTA\" -- FROM 
ONE\'S SUPERIORS. THIS STIFLES INITIATIVE AND GIVES UNDUE 
EMPHASIS TO THE CAUTIONARY APPROACH. THIS APPLIES TO ALL OF 
THE ABOVE-MENTIONED PERSONS. END NOTE.) 
 
-------------------------------- 
GETTING THEM TO PLAY ON OUR TEAM 
-------------------------------- 
 
11.  (SBU)  THE VATICAN IS POTENTIALLY A VALUABLE ALLY IN THE 
PUBLIC DIPLOMACY EFFORT TO PROMOTE BROADER ACCEPTANCE OF 
BIOTECHNOLOGY AND GMOS AMONG OUR KEY TRADING PARTNERS. ITS 
MORAL CLOUT STILL INFLUENCES MANY NATIONS IN THE EU, AND 
PARTICULARLY IN THE DEVELOPING WORLD, WHERE, IN CERTAIN 
INSTANCES, INDIVIDUAL CLERGY ANTAGONISTIC TO PROFIT-MAKING 
MULTINATIONAL CORPORATIONS HELP BEAT THE ANTI-GMO DRUMS. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  02268  02 OF 03  100540Z 
VATICAN BACKING FOR BIOTECHNOLOGY AND GMOS AS A MEANS TO FEED 
THE WORLD\'S POOR WOULD HAVE A SIGNIFICANT IMPACT ON CHANGING 
THE GENERALLY FEARFUL EUROPEAN MINDSET BY UNDERCUTTING A KEY 
RATIONALE OF ANTI-BIOTECH ACTIVISTS (THAT U.S. COMPANIES WILL 
DISPLACE TRADITIONAL METHODS OF AGRICULTURE ACROSS THE 
WORLD).  POST\'S EFFORTS TO EXPOSE VATICAN PROTAGONISTS TO THE 
SCIENCE HAVE BEEN RELATIVELY SUCCESSFUL. FOR EXAMPLE, IN JULY 
2001 WE ORGANIZED A PANEL DISCUSSION BETWEEN VISITING GMO 
EXPERT C.S. PRAKASH OF TUSKEEGEE UNIVERSITY AND MEMBERS OF 
THE PONTIFICAL ACADEMY OF THE SCIENCES (PAS) AND THE 
PONTIFICAL ACADEMY FOR LIFE (PAL).  AMBASSADOR FOLLOWED THAT 
WITH A DINNER IHO DR. PRAKASH IN FEBRUARY 2002, ATTENDED BY 
VATICAN FM TAURAN AND SEVERAL SENIOR VATICAN OFFICIALS. 
 
12.  (SBU) EMBASSY VATICAN IS BUILDING ON THIS FOUNDATION 
FOLLOWING OUR BIOTECHNOLOGY ACTION PLAN WORKED IN 
COORDINATION WITH EMBASSY ROME AND THE US MISSION TO THE UN 
FOOD AND AGRICULTURAL AGENCIES. OUR PART OF THE PLAN 
ENVISAGES: 
 
-- AMBASSADOR REGULARLY REMARKING ON GMO POTENTIAL FOR 
PROMOTING DEVELOPING WORLD FOOD SECURITY DURING HIS 
VATICAN-RELATED PUBLIC AND PRIVATE ENGAGEMENTS (E.G. HIS 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
