SUBJECT: THE LIMITS OF VATICAN PERSUASION ON BISHOPS\' 
POLITICAL VIEWS 
 
UNITY OF THE CHURCH AND THE SECURITY OF THE FAITHFUL IN 
THOSE COUNTRIES WHERE CATHOLICS ARE A MINORITY (IN THIS 
CASE, IN NEIGHBORING BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA). 
 
6. (SBU) COMMENT:  WHEN CONFRONTED WITH A BISHOP WHOSE VIEWS 
GO AGAINST THE GRAIN OF THE HOLY SEE\'S VIEWS ON SECULAR 
POLITICAL ISSUES, THE HOLY SEE WILL ALWAYS ASSESS ITS OWN 
BIG PICTURE OF FAITH, MORALS, DOCTRINE AND THE WELL-BEING OF 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  03636  02 OF 02  231502Z 
ITS FAITHFUL IN JUDGING WHETHER AND HOW TO INTERVENE.  THE 
HOLY SEE WILL ALMOST ALWAYS CHOOSE TO ACT BEHIND THE SCENES, 
APPROACHING AN OUTSPOKEN BISHOP THROUGH HIS COLLEAGUES IN 
THE LOCAL BISHOPS\' CONFERENCE AND/OR THE LOCAL NUNCIO.  IN 
CASES WHERE BISHOPS OF OTHER CHURCH REPRESENTATIVES 
ARTICULATE VIEWS SEEN AS DAMAGING TO U.S. INTERESTS, 
EMBASSIES SHOULD SEEK TO DEVELOP GOOD AVENUES OF 
COMMUNICATION WITH THE RESIDENT NUNCIO AND THE NATIONAL 
BISHOPS THEMSELVES.  EMBASSY VATICAN WOULD ALSO BE PREPARED 
TO APPROACH THE SECRETARIAT OF STATE AT THE HOLY SEE AND TO 
ADVISE POSTS ON HOW BEST TO ADVANCE U.S. VIEWS IN THE FACE 
OF OUTSPOKEN OPPOSITION FROM LOCAL BISHOPS. 
 
NICHOLSON 
 
