TAGS: PREL, EAID, EAGR, VT 
SUBJECT: THE ZAMBIAN MAIZE CRISIS:  MOVING THE HOLY SEE TO 
\"YES\" ON BIOTECH AGRICULTURE 
 
FOOD ASSISTANCE AND THE DANGEROUS PRECEDENT THAT WOULD BE SET 
BY THE ZAMBIAN REJECTION OF U.S. MAIZE, POLOFF INSISTED THAT 
THE ISSUE WAS FAR BROADER, WITH POTENTIALLY DISASTROUS 
CONSEQUENCES FOR HUNGRY PEOPLE AROUND THE WORLD.  CAVINA WAS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  04361  02 OF 03  081059Z 
NON-COMMITTAL, NOTING THAT THE HOLY SEE HAD A DELICATE 
RELATIONSHIP WITH PRESIDENT MWANAWASA, A SEVENTH DAY 
ADVENTIST.  CAVINA RELATED THAT THE ZAMBIAN GOVERNMENT HAD 
JUST LAST JULY COLLUDED IN A \"BAIT AND SWITCH\" SETUP OF THE 
PAPAL NUNCIO OVER THE ARCHBISHOP MALINGO ISSUE. (NOTE: 
MALINGO IS THE POPULIST FAITH HEALING ZAMBIAN ARCHBISHOP WHO 
ALMOST GOT HIMSELF EXCOMMUNICATED LAST YEAR AFTER \"MARRYING\" 
KOREAN DIVORCEE MARIA SUNG IN A MASS UNIFICATION CHURCH 
CEREMONY IN NEW YORK. SUNG, NOW HIS EX-\"WIFE,\" CURRENTLY 
RESIDES IN LUSAKA AND, ACCORDING TO CAVINA, AMBUSHED THE 
NUNCIO IN FRONT OF TV CAMERAS INSIDE THE ZAMBIAN MFA. END 
NOTE.) 
 
-------- 
COMMENT: 
-------- 
 
7. (C) FOR THE PAST EIGHTEEN MONTHS POST HAS WORKED TO GET TO 
HOLY SEE TO BUILD ON ITS CAUTIOUSLY OPTIMISTIC PUBLIC STANCE 
TOWARDS BIOTECHNOLOGY. IN OUR VIEW, A STRONG PUBLIC STANCE IN 
SUPPORT OF AGRICULTURAL BIOTECHNOLOGY IS A NATURAL FOR ANYONE 
INTERESTED IN PROMOTING FOOD SECURITY IN THE DEVELOPING 
WORLD.  THE ZAMBIAN FOOD CRISIS, AS TRAGIC AS IT IS, MAY 
PRESENT A \"DEFINING MOMENT\" FOR OUR BIOTECH DIALOGUE WITH THE 
HOLY SEE.  NOBODY, AND ESPECIALLY NOT THE POPE, CAN ARGUE 
THAT A PRECAUTIONARY PRINCIPLE SHOULD APPLY WHEN IT MEANS 
REAL HUMAN BEINGS WILL GO HUNGRY OR EVEN STARVE.  WITH U.S. 
FOOD AID SO VITAL TO ADDRESSING THE SOUTHERN AFRICAN FOOD 
CRISIS, THE HOLY SEE SHOULD BE SINGING FROM THE SAME SHEET 
WITH US. WE ARE, IN FACT, COORDINATING POSITIONS AT THE UN ON 
A CONVENTION TO BAN ALL FORMS OF HUMAN CLONING -- THE \"FLIP 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  04361  02 OF 03  081059Z 
SIDE\" OF THE GMO FOOD DEBATE.  POST BELIEVES THAT THE TIME IS 
RIGHT FOR A HIGH-LEVEL APPROACH, WHICH COULD NUDGE THE HOLY 
SEE OFF THE FENCE, AT LEAST AS REGARDS THE SAFETY FOR HUMAN 
CONSUMPTION OF BIOTECH FOODS.  WHILE ANY HOLY SEE STATEMENT 
WOULD DOUBTLESS BE CAREFULLY WORDED AND NOT ERASE VATICAN 
CONCERNS AT ENVIRONMENTAL DANGERS FROM BIOTECH CROPS, IT 
COULD GREATLY FACILITATE OUR BROADER EFFORT TO ERODE EUROPEAN 
AND OTHER INTERNATIONAL OBJECTIONS TO AND MISUNDERSTANDINGS 
OF BIOTECH FOODS.  (NOTE: WE WILL NEED TO ADDRESS THE HOLY 
SEE\'S CONCERNS AT POSSIBLE ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS OF GMO CROPS 
IN THE FUTURE, AND POST HAS AN ACTION PLAN FOR THAT TO BE 
REPORTED SEPTEL. END NOTE.) 
 
8. (SBU)  POST REQUESTS THAT SECRETARY POWELL CONSIDER 
SENDING VATICAN FM ARCHBISHOP JEAN LOUIS TAURAN A LETTER 
URGING THE HOLY SEE TO ISSUE A STATEMENT THAT TRACKS WITH THE 
EXISTING UN AND EC STATEMENTS ON BIOTECH FOOD SAFETY. POST 
OFFERS BELOW SUGGESTED LANGUAGE FOR A POWELL/TAURAN LETTER, 
SUBSTANTIALLY DRAWN FROM THE LARSON/DIOUF LETTER TRANSMITTED 
IN REF E. 
 
9. (SBU)  PROPOSED LANGUAGE FOR LETTER TO VATICAN FM TAURAN, 
BEGIN TEXT: 
 
YOUR EXCELLENCY, 
 
THE UNITED STATES IS DEEPLY CONCERNED AT THE UNFOLDING 
HUMANITARIAN CRISIS IN SOUTHERN AFRICA.  I KNOW THAT HOLY 
SEE, WHERE THE CENTRALITY OF THE HUMAN PERSON IS OF PARAMOUNT 
CONCERN, SHARES OUR CONCERN ABOUT THE MILLIONS OF AFRICAN 
LIVES NOW AT RISK FROM HUNGER AND STARVATION. 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  04361  02 OF 03  081059Z 
 
THE UNITED STATES IS CURRENTLY SEEKING TO HELP PROVIDE SAFE 
FOOD TO ALL THOSE IN NEED -- IN SOUTHERN AFRICA AND ELSEWHERE 
WHERE NEEDS ARE GREAT.  THE UNITED STATES PROVIDES 
SIXTY-THREE PERCENT OF THE FOOD ASSISTANCE GIVEN TO THE WORLD 
FOOD PROGRAM, AND ALREADY THE UNITED STATES HAS PROVIDED OVER 
SEVENTY PERCENT OF THE FOOD ASSISTANCE ON THE GROUND IN 
SOUTHERN AFRICA.  THERE IS NO ALTERNATIVE SUPPLY TO REPLACE 
THE RISING NEED FOR FOOD TO AVOID MASS STARVATION IN THIS 
REGION.  UNFORTUNATELY, SOME INDIVIDUALS AND ORGANIZATIONS, 
INCLUDING SOME ELEMENTS OF THE CATHOLIC CHURCH, HAVE ARGUED 
AGAINST DISTRIBUTING U.S. FOOD ASSISTANCE BECAUSE IT CANNOT 
BE GUARANTEED TO BE FREE OF \"TRANSGENIC\" SEEDS. 
 
THE UNITED STATES IS DEEPLY CONCERNED THAT CONFUSION ABOUT 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
