SUBJECT: THE ZAMBIAN MAIZE CRISIS:  MOVING THE HOLY SEE TO 
\"YES\" ON BIOTECH AGRICULTURE 
 
THE SAFETY OF THESE FOOD PRODUCTS 
-- THE SAME FOOD AS IS CONSUMED BY MILLIONS OF AMERICANS 
EVERY DAY -- WILL LEAD TO FURTHER HUNGER AND STARVATION.  WE 
KNOW THAT COUNTRIES WISH TO MAKE INFORMED CHOICES ABOUT FOOD 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  04361  03 OF 03  081059Z 
SAFETY FOR THE GOOD OF THEIR PEOPLE.  THE SCIENCE ON THESE 
FOOD PRODUCTS IS CLEAR:  BIOTECH FOODS AVAILABLE TODAY ARE AS 
SAFE TO CONSUME AS ARE THEIR CONVENTIONAL COUNTERPARTS. 
 
THE UNITED NATIONS, WORLD HEALTH ORGANIZATION, AND THE 
EUROPEAN COMMISSION AMONG OTHER ORGANIZATIONS HAVE RECENTLY 
ISSUED STATEMENTS SUPPORTING THIS VIEW.  THE UNITED STATES 
BELIEVES THAT A CLEAR AND UNAMBIGUOUS STATEMENT FROM THE HOLY 
SEE, A MORAL LEADER WHOSE VOICE IS RESPECTED THE WORLD OVER, 
REGARDING THE SAFETY OF GENETICALLY MODIFIED FOODS WOULD 
GREATLY HELP TO OVERCOME PREVAILING HESITATIONS IN AFRICA AND 
BEYOND.  IN THIS WAY, THE HOLY SEE COULD MAKE A POSITIVE 
CONTRIBUTION TO ALLEVIATING THE SUFFERING OF HUNGRY PEOPLE 
NOT JUST IN SOUTHERN AFRICA, BUT EVERYWHERE PEOPLE RECEIVE 
FOOD ASSISTANCE. 
 
IF WE CAN WORK TOGETHER TO OVERCOME THIS GRAVE CRISIS OF 
HUMAN SUFFERING IN SOUTHERN AFRICA, WE CAN THEN TURN OUR 
ATTENTION TO REVITALIZING AFRICAN AGRICULTURE AND 
PRODUCTIVITY TO PREVENT FUTURE CRISES.  I LOOK FORWARD TO A 
POSITIVE COLLABORATION ON THIS VITAL MATTER. 
 
SINCERELY, 
COLIN POWELL 
SECRETARY OF STATE 
 
