"3714","9/13/2002 4:55","02VATICAN4444","Embassy Vatican","CONFIDENTIAL","02STATE169975","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 01 OF 02 VATICAN 004444 
 
SIPDIS 
 
FOR EUR, EUR/PD, AND EUR/EEA -KALLEGRONE 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 09/12/2012 
TAGS: IZ, KPAO, OPRC, PREL, KPAO, OPRC, PREL, VT, VTIZ 
SUBJECT: HOLY SEE AND THE ROADMAP FOR IRAQ PUBLIC DIPLOMACY 
 
REF: A. A) STATE 169975 
 
     B. B) VATICAN 4398 
     C. C) VATICAN 4388 
     D. D) VATICAN 0444 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: CHARGE D\'AFFAIRES, D. BRENT HARDT 
 
1. (C) SUMMARY:  THE HOLY SEE PRESENTS DISTINCTIVE CHALLENGES 
AND OPPORTUNITIES IN REGARD TO IRAQ PUBLIC DIPLOMACY.  UNLIKE 
MOST POSTS, OUR \"PUBLIC\" WITHIN THE VATICAN IS LIMITED, BUT 
THE PUBLIC REACH OF THE VATICAN IS TRULY GLOBAL AND AMONG THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  04444  01 OF 02  130613Z 
MOST IMPORTANT VOICES WE CAN SEEK TO INFLUENCE.  AS WE HAVE 
RECENTLY REPORTED (REFS B AND C), THE HOLY SEE IS CONCERNED 
ABOUT THE IRAQI REGIME, BUT OPPOSED TO MILITARY ACTION BASED 
ON THE INFORMATION THEY HAVE AT THIS TIME.  DESPITE ITS 
TRADITIONAL OPPOSITION TO THE USE OF FORCE, THE HOLY SEE\'S 
FOREIGN MINISTER DID LEAVE OPEN THE POSSIBILITY OF MILITARY 
ACTION, BUT ONLY AFTER CONSIDERING THE IMPLICATIONS FOR THE 
IRAQI PEOPLE THE REGION, AND GLOBAL STABILITY, AND ONLY 
WITHIN A U.N. FRAMEWORK.  OUR FIRST PUBLIC DIPLOMACY 
CHALLENGE IS THEREFORE TO MAKE OUR CASE FOR ACTION TO THE 
POPE AND SENIOR VATICAN OFFICIALS.  END SUMMARY. 
 
--------------- 
MAKING OUR CASE 
--------------- 
 
2. (C) THE HOLY SEE RECOGNIZES THE SECURITY RISK POSED BY 
WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION, AND THE THREATS SADDAM POSES TO 
HIS PEOPLE AND THE REGION.  THEY DO NOT NEED TO BE CONVINCED 
OF THE NATURE OF SADDAM\'S CHARACTER, HIS HISTORY IN POWER, OR 
THE POTENTIAL RISKS THAT HE POSES.  WHAT HAS BEEN LACKING, 
FROM THE HOLY SEE\'S PERSPECTIVE, BASED ON RECENT DISCUSSIONS 
AND PRESENTATIONS BY SENIOR VATICAN OFFICIALS, IS THE 
FOLLOWING: 
 
-- A CLEAR UNDERSTANDING AS TO WHY IRAQ CANNOT BE CONTAINED 
SHORT OF DIRECT MILITARY ACTION; 
 
-- COMPELLING JUSTIFICATION AS TO WHY THE THREAT FROM IRAQ IS 
GREATER TODAY THAN DURING THE PAST SO THAT IT WOULD REQUIRE 
IMMEDIATE ACTION; 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  04444  01 OF 02  130613Z 
 
-- A COMPREHENSIVE ASSESSMENT OF THE RISKS AND POTENTIAL TO 
THE IRAQI PEOPLE, THE REGION, AND GLOBAL STABILITY OF BOTH 
TAKING ACTION VERSUS NOT TAKING ACTION (THE HOLY SEE BELIEVES 
THERE IS A GREAT RISK THAT MILITARY ACTION IN THE REGION 
COULD LEAD TO A MUCH LARGER CONFLAGRATION THAT COULD DRAW 
ISRAEL INTO WAR IN WAYS THAT COULD BE POTENTIALLY 
DEVASTATING); 
 
-- A CONVINCING CASE THAT THE WORLD COMMUNITY HAS EXHAUSTED 
ALL OPTIONS AND MUST ACT TO AVERT A GREATER CALAMITY. 
 
----------------------------- 
ADDRESSING THE JUST WAR ISSUE 
----------------------------- 
 
3. (C)  ULTIMATELY, THE HOLY SEE\'S PUBLIC STANCE ON AN 
INTERNATIONAL RESPONSE TO IRAQ -- IN PARTICULAR WHETHER IT 
WILL EITHER ACQUIESCE IN OR SUPPORT MILITARY ACTION IN IRAQ 
-- WILL DEPEND ON WHETHER SUCH A RESPONSE MEETS THE HOLY 
SEE\'S JUST WAR DOCTRINE AS ENUNCIATED IN THE CATHOLIC 
CATECHISM.  TO THE EXTENT THAT U.S. DIPLOMATIC AND PUBLIC 
DIPLOMACY EFFORTS CAN MAKE THE CASE THAT SUCH ACTION MEETS 
THE JUST WAR CRITERIA, THE PROSPECTS FOR VATICAN 
ACKNOWLEDGMENT OF THE NEED FOR ACTION WILL BE GREATER.  REF D 
OUTLINES THE JUST WAR DOCTRINE AND HIGHLIGHTS THE VALUE OF 
WORKING WITH THE HOLY SEE AS WE MOVE FORWARD TO BUILD 
INTERNATIONAL SUPPORT FOR OUR CASE AGAINST IRAQ. 
 
4. (C) THE KEY ELEMENTS OF THE JUST WAR THEORY THAT WOULD 
NEED TO BE ADDRESSED TO MAKE INROADS WITH THE HOLY SEE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  04444  01 OF 02  130613Z 
INCLUDE THE FOLLOWING: 
 
-- ANY MILITARY RESPONSE TO AN EVIL SHOULD NOT LEAD TO A 
GREATER EVIL. 
 
FM TAURAN REITERATED THIS SEPTEMBER 10 (REF B) IN AN 
IMPORTANT INTERVIEW IN THE ITALIAN, CHURCH-RELATED WEEKLY 
AVVENIRE.  THIS TIES IN WITH THE HOLY SEE\'S CONCERN ABOUT 
MILITARY ACTION PROVOKING A BROADER REGIONAL CONFLAGRATION, 
AND ITS FEAR FOR THE LIVES OF INNOCENTS THAT ANY MILITARY 
CONFLICT ENTAILS. 
 
-- ANY FORCE USED SHOULD BE PROPORTIONAL TO THE DESIRED END. 
 
IN THIS REGARD, THE HOLY SEE WOULD NEITHER ACQUIESCE IN NOR 
SUPPORT A MILITARY AIR CAMPAIGN THAT RESULTED IN MASSIVE 
IRAQI CIVILIAN CASUALTIES. 
 
-- JUST WAR CAN ONLY BE WAGED BY A LEGAL AUTHORITY. 
 
THE DEFINITION OF A LEGAL AUTHORITY IS OPEN TO DEBATE, BUT FM 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL     PTQ3119 
 
PAGE 01        VATICA  04444  02 OF 02  130613Z 
ACTION EUR-00 
 
INFO  LOG-00   NP-00    AMAD-00  ACQ-00   CIAE-00  INL-00   DODE-00 
      DS-00    VC-00    TEDE-00  INR-00   IO-00    LAB-01   VCE-00 
      NEA-00   DCP-01   NSAE-00  IRM-00   USIE-00  DSCC-00  DRL-02 
      SAS-00     /004W 
                  ------------------E6BE02  130613Z /38 
P 130455Z SEP 02 
