TO SECSTATE WASHDC PRIORITY 
 
C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 02 OF 02 VATICAN 004444 
 
SIPDIS 
 
FOR EUR, EUR/PD, AND EUR/EEA -KALLEGRONE 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 09/12/2012 
TAGS: IZ, KPAO, OPRC, PREL, VT 
SUBJECT: HOLY SEE AND THE ROADMAP FOR IRAQ PUBLIC DIPLOMACY 
 
TAURAN\'S INSISTENCE THAT ANY MILITARY ACTION IN IRAQ \"SHOULD 
ONLY BE TAKEN AFTER A DECISION TAKEN IN THE UN FRAMEWORK,\" 
MAKES CLEAR THAT IN THIS CASE THE HOLY SEE REGARDS THE U.N. 
AS THE RELEVANT LEGAL AUTHORITY TO SANCTION ANY MILITARY MOVE 
AGAINST SADDAM. 
 
-- ALL OTHER REMEDIES MUST BE EXHAUSTED BEFORE RESORT TO 
MILITARY FORCE. 
 
TAURAN AND OTHER OFFICIALS HAVE QUESTIONED WHETHER RECOURSE 
TO THE MILITARY OPTION IS THE ONLY OPTION AVAILABLE TO THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  04444  02 OF 02  130613Z 
WORLD COMMUNITY OR THE MOST APPROPRIATE MEANS TO ENSURE A 
TRUE PEACE.  THE HOLY SEE PREFERS DIALOGUE AND ENGAGEMENT 
WITHIN A FRAMEWORK OF INTERNATIONAL LAW, AND CLEARLY WOULD 
LIKE TO SEE THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY PURSUE OTHER FORMS OF 
PRESSURE MORE EXHAUSTIVELY BEFORE MOVING TO A MILITARY OPTION. 
 
------------------------------------------ 
INFLUENCING THE HOLY SEE\'S PUBLIC POSITION 
------------------------------------------ 
 
5. (C) THE HOLY SEE NATURALLY VIEWS ITS ROLE AS THAT OF AN 
INTERNATIONAL VOICE FOR PEACE AND RECONCILIATION AND A 
\"BUILDER OF BRIDGES\" BETWEEN PEOPLES.  IN ADDITION, THE POPE 
HAS LABORED HARD TO AVOID A GLOBAL DRIFT TOWARD A \"CLASH OF 
CIVILIZATIONS.\"  THIS CONCERN NOT ONLY REFLECTS THE HOLY 
SEE\'S TRADITIONAL CONCERN FOR THE PHYSICAL SAFETY OF 
CATHOLICS IN COUNTRIES WHERE THEY ARE A MINORITY, BUT ALSO 
ITS ROLE AS A MORAL AND SPIRITUAL  VOICE FOR MANKIND.  AS A 
FIRST STEP IN BUILDING SUPPORT WITHIN THE HOLY SEE, WE 
REITERATE OUR REQUEST FOR SENIOR LEVEL BRIEFINGS THE 
RATIONALE FOR ACTION, THE POTENTIAL IMPACT OF ACTION ON THE 
REGION, AND PROSPECTS FOR STABILITY AFTER MILITARY ACTION. 
 
6. (C) IN THE SAME WAY THE USG DEVELOPED A MUTUALLY 
BENEFICIAL DIALOGUE WITH POPE JOHN PAUL II DURING THE COLD 
WAR, POST BELIEVES A SIMILAR DIALOGUE ON THE INTERNATIONAL 
RESPONSE TO TERRORISM WOULD OFFER SIMILAR MUTUAL BENEFITS. 
HIGH-LEVEL BRIEFINGS WOULD UNDERSCORE OUR DEEP REFLECTION ON 
THE MATTER AND LAY THE GROUNDWORK FOR FURTHER POSITIVE 
DIALOGUE. 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  04444  02 OF 02  130613Z 
7. (C) BEYOND SUCH DIRECT USG ENGAGEMENT, U.S. EXPERTS ON 
JUST WAR SUCH AS MICHAEL NOVAK ALREADY HAVE A STRONG 
REPUTATION WITHIN THE HOLY SEE.  A PUBLIC DIPLOMACY CAMPAIGN 
SHOULD SEEK TO HIGHLIGHT THEIR VIEWS AND PERHAPS EVEN SOLICIT 
THEM AS SPEAKERS AND INTERLOCUTORS FOR THE EMBASSY AND HOLY 
SEE.  IN ADDITION, PROMINENT FOREIGN POLICY AUTHORITIES SUCH 
AS HENRY KISSINGER AND ZBIGNIEW BREZEZINSKI HAVE INDEPENDENT 
ACCESS TO THE HOLY SEE AND SHOULD BE ENCOURAGED TO SHARE 
THEIR VIEWS ON IRAQ AND THE NEED TO RESPOND TO TERRORISM 
DIRECTLY. 
 
HARDT 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
> 
 

