BEEN \"UPSET AND PERPLEXED.\"  TAURAN NOTED THAT THIS \"WOULD 
HAVE BEEN A REASON FOR GREAT DISTURBANCE IN THE REGION.\" THE 
AMBASSADOR POINTED OUT THAT THE PRESIDENT\'S DECISION WAS MADE 
IN THE FACE OF CONSIDERABLE CONGRESSIONAL PRESSURE. 
 
