PAGE 02        VATICA  00283  04 OF 05  241035Z 
VT 
SUBJECT: PARTNERS FOR PROGRESS - WORKING WITH VATICAN 
DEVELOPMENT AGENCIES 
 
MADE FOR THE POOREST, WEAKEST OR MOST MARGINALIZED MEMBERS 
OF SOCIETY.  CARITAS DOES THIS THROUGH PUBLIC CAMPAIGNING 
AND DIRECT LOBBYING OF GOVERNMENTS AND INSTITUTIONS.  THE 
CURRENT ADVOCACY ISSUES INCLUDE PALESTINE AND ISRAEL, IRAQI 
SANCTIONS AND POSSIBLE WAR, THE UN CONFERENCE ON FINANCING 
FOR DEVELOPMENT, THE CRISIS IN SIERRA LEONE, INTERNATIONAL 
DEBT, AND TRADE FAIRNESS. 
 
12.  (U) HIGH-PROFILE MEMBERS OF THE CARITAS FEDERATION 
INCLUDE U.S. CATHOLIC RELIEF SERVICES (CRS) AND U.K. CAFOD. 
BOTH AGENCIES HAVE EXTENSIVE INTERNATIONAL DEVELOPMENT 
PROGRAMS.  FOR EXAMPLE, CRS WORK WITH LOCAL PARTNERS AND 
OTHER INTERNATIONAL HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS TO RESPOND TO 
PRESENT FOOD SHORTAGES IN SOUTHERN AFRICA AND AVERT A FAMINE 
IN THE REGION.  AT PRESENT, THE AGENCY PLANS TO DISTRIBUTE 
MORE THAN 45,000 METRIC TONS OF FOOD, SUCH AS MAIZE, FLOUR 
AND VEGETABLE OIL, TO NEARLY 400,000 FAMILIES IN THE REGION. 
CRS IS ALSO TARGETING ITS RESPONSE TO COMMUNITIES WHERE IT 
HAS EXISTING PROGRAMS DEALING WITH HIV/AIDS -- SUPPLYING 
FOOD TO THE MOST VULNERABLE: CHILD-HEADED HOUSEHOLDS, 
PREGNANT AND LACTATING MOTHERS AND CHILDREN UNDER FIVE. 
 
13.  (U) UK-BASED CAFOD IS ALSO ACTIVELY ENGAGED IN 
DEVELOPMENT WORK IN SOUTHERN AFRICA - PARTICULARLY IN 
FEEDING AND HIV/AIDS PREVENTION AND TREATMENT.  THE AGENCY\'S 
PROGRAMS IN THE REGION ARE ALREADY FEEDING HUNDREDS OF 
THOUSANDS OF THE MOST VULNERABLE PEOPLE IN ZIMBABWE, MALAWI, 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  00283  04 OF 05  241035Z 
ANGOLA, MOZAMBIQUE AND SWAZILAND.  CAFOD HAS ALSO LAUNCHED A 
SPECIAL APPEAL FOR SOUTHERN AFRICA, RESULTING IN MILLIONS OF 
DOLLARS IN DONATIONS.  CAFOD IS USING NOURISHMENT TO HELP 
AIDS SUFFERERS LIVE WITH THE CONDITION.  CARE PROGRAMS 
CONDUCTED IN PARTNERSHIP WITH LOCAL CHURCH AGENCIES PROVIDE 
HIGH-PROTEIN BALANCED DIETS TO PATIENTS AS A WAY TO STAY 
HEALTHY.  THE PROGRAMS HOWEVER, ARE THREATENED BY THE 
ESCALATING SOUTHERN AFRICAN FOOD CRISIS. 
 
14.  (U) OTHER CARITAS FEDERATION MEMBERS IN FIRST WORLD 
COUNTRIES IN WESTERN EUROPE AND AUSTRALASIA UNDERTAKE 
SIMILAR PROGRAMS THROUGHOUT THE WORLD -- PREFERABLY WORKING 
IN PARTNERSHIP WITH LOCAL AGENCIES AND CHURCH-BASED GROUPS - 
- TO FOSTER ACCOUNTABILITY AND TRANSPARENCY. 
 
---------------------------- 
THE COMMUNITY OF SANT\'EGIDIO 
---------------------------- 
 
15.  (U) THIS ROME-BASED INTERNATIONAL VOLUNTEER 
ORGANIZATION IS INVOLVED IN NUMEROUS CHARITABLE AND 
DEVELOPMENT ACTIVITIES AT NATIONAL AND INTERNATIONAL LEVELS 
AND HAS BEEN NICKNAMED \"THE POPE\'S UNITED NATIONS\".  HAVING 
GAINED INTERNATIONAL RECOGNITION FOR ITS WORK IN ENDING THE 
MOZAMBIQUE CONFLICT, IT ALSO CONDUCTS LOWER-PROFILE BUT 
VITAL DEVELOPMENT WORK, ESPECIALLY IN AFRICA.  THE FIRST, A 
FOOD RELIEF PROGRAM IN ONE OF MALAWI\'S MOST ISOLATED AND 
POOR AREAS PROVIDES NON-PERISHABLE HIGH PROTEIN FOOD SUCH AS 
RICE, BEANS, OIL, SUGAR AND VITAMIN-ENRICHED BISCUITS FOR 
CHILDREN.  THE SECOND, AN HIV/AIDS PREVENTION AND TREATMENT 
PROGRAM IN MOZAMBIQUE, PROVIDES TESTING, LOCAL STAFF 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  00283  04 OF 05  241035Z 
TRAINING, HEALTH EDUCATION, ANTI-RETROVIRAL THERAPY, 
MONITORING OF BLOOD DONATIONS, PREVENTION AND CARE OF AIDS- 
LINKED DISEASES, NUTRITIONAL SUSTENANCE TO AIDS SUFFERS AND 
HOME CARE FOR THE SERIOUSLY ILL.  SANT\'EGIDIO HAS APPROACHED 
EMBASSY AND STATE DEPARTMENT/AID FOR SUPPORT.  EMBASSY 
STRONGLY SUPPORTS SUCH REQUESTS AND WILL SOLICIT FUNDING 
SEPTEL. 
 
--------------------------------- 
LOCAL CHURCH AND RELIGIOUS ORDERS 
--------------------------------- 
 
16.  (U) MANY RELIGIOUS ORDERS AND LOCAL CHURCH GROUPS 
AROUND THE WORLD PROVIDE DEVELOPMENT SERVICES SUCH SCHOOLS 
AND UNIVERSITIES, AGRICULTURAL TECHNOLOGY, HEALTH CARE AND 
VOCATIONAL TRAINING.  THE LARGER RELIGIOUS ORDERS, SUCH AS 
THE JESUITS ALSO HAVE SPECIALIST AGENCIES.  THE JESUIT 
REFUGEE SERVICE (JRS) WORKS IN OVER 40 COUNTRIES, WITH A 
MISSION TO ACCOMPANY, SERVE AND DEFEND THE RIGHTS OF 
REFUGEES AND FORCIBLY DISPLACED PEOPLE.  JRS ALSO PROVIDES 
SHELTER, EDUCATION, AND MEDICAL CARE FOR PEOPLE WHO ARE 
DRIVEN FROM THEIR HOMES BY CONFLICT, HUMANITARIAN DISASTER 
OR VIOLATION OF HUMAN RIGHTS.  JRS UNDERTAKES SERVICES AT 
NATIONAL AND REGIONAL LEVEL WITH THE SUPPORT OF AN 
 
