UNCLAS SECTION 02 OF 02 VATICAN 000402 
 
SIPDIS 
 
DEPT. FOR EUR/WE-MENNUTI, EB, AND AF/S 
 
E.O. 12958: N/A 
TAGS: EAGR, EAID, PREL, VT, ZA 
SUBJECT: HOLY SEE FOREIGN MINISTER TAURAN PLEDGES TO 
CLARIFY HOLY SEE\'S POSITION ON BIOTECH FOODS IN ZAMBIA AND 
SOUTHERN AFRICA 
 
- THE GMO\'S COMING FROM THE U.S. ARE NOT IDENTIFIED AS SUCH, 
SINCE THE POLICY OF THE U.S. DOES NOT REQUIRE IT.  HOWEVER 
THE CONSUMER HAS THE RIGHT TO KNOW; 
 
- THE REASON FOR THE U.S. PRESSURE IN THIS MATTER IS BECAUSE 
THERE IS A SURPLUS OF GMO. 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  00402  02 OF 02  030859Z 
 
5.  IN LIGHT OF THESE POSITIONS, TAURAN AGREED WITH THE 
AMBASSADOR ON THE NEED TO ENSURE THAT THE HOLY SEE\'S MORE 
BALANCED POSITION WAS WIDELY DISSEMINATED IN THE COUNTRY AND 
REGIONS.  HE PROMISED TO ENSURE THE RESULTS OF THE PONTIFICAL 
ACADEMY OF SCIENCE\'S POSITION -- WHICH SEES NO REASON FOR 
REJECTION OF BIOTECH FOODS AND THEY SHOULD BE PROVIDED TO 
DEVELOPING COUNTRY POPULATIONS AS LONG AS THE PRECAUTIONARY 
PRINCIPAL IS OBSERVED (AS IT IS WITH PHARMACEUTICALS) -- ARE 
PROVIDED TO ALL THE BISHOPS.  THE HOLY SEE WOULD THEN 
ENCOURAGE THE BISHOPS TO ISSUE A STATEMENT AND DISSEMINATE 
THE WORD IN THEIR CHURCHES.  TAURAN ADDED THAT IF THE BISHOPS 
FAILED TO DO SO -- WHICH IS POSSIBLE GIVEN THAT THE HOLY SEE 
CANNOT ORDER BISHOPS TO TAKE SPECIFIC STANDS ON POLITICAL 
ISSUES -- HE WOULD HAVE THE NUNCIO TAKE STEPS TO GET THE HOLY 
SEE\'S POSITION OUT. 
 
6.  THE AMBASSADOR THANKED TAURAN FOR HIS COMMITMENT TO 
ENSURE THE HOLY SEE\'S POSITION WAS DISSEMINATED MORE WIDELY 
IN ZAMBIA AND THE REST OF SOUTHERN AFRICA, BUT STRESSED THE 
IMPORTANCE OF MOVING QUICKLY GIVEN THE STILL PRESENT THREAT 
OF FAMINE IN THE COUNTRY.  WHILE THE AMBASSADOR RECOGNIZED 
THAT THE WORLD FOOD PROGRAM HAD TAKEN STEPS TO WORK AROUND 
THE ZAMBIAN GOVERNMENT\'S REJECTION OF U.S. AID, THE 
AMBASSADOR STRESSED THE INCREASED COSTS AND TIME THIS HAD 
IMPOSED ON THE RELIEF EFFORT.  HE ALSO NOTED THAT OUR 
INFORMATION WAS NOT AS SANGUINE AS THAT PRESENTED BY THE 
NUNCIO, ALTHOUGH FOOD NOW APPEARED TO BE IN THE PIPELINE. 
BEYOND THE IMMEDIATE SITUATION, HOWEVER, THE AMBASSADOR 
POINTED OUT THAT THE ZAMBIAN DECISION REPRESENTED A NEGATIVE 
PRECEDENT WITH POTENTIALLY SERIOUS IMPLICATIONS FOR BROADER 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  00402  02 OF 02  030859Z 
AFRICAN RELIEF IF MORE COUNTRIES BEGAN FOLLOWING ZAMBIA\'S 
LEAD AND REJECTED U.S. FOOD.  GIVEN THAT THE U.S. PROVIDES 
OVER 60 PERCENT OF ALL RELIEF FOOD TO THE REGION, THE 
AMBASSADOR NOTED, SUCH RESTRICTIONS WOULD MAKE IT IMPOSSIBLE 
FOR HE WFP TO MEET ITS DEMANDS).  TAURAN AGREED THAT SUCH A 
PRECEDENT WOULD BE UNFORTUNATE, AND CONTRARY TO EFFORTS TO 
FEED THOSE IN NEED. 
 
------- 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
7.  THE HOLY SEE\'S RESPONSE ON THIS ISSUE, ABOUT WHICH THE 
EMBASSY HAS BEEN PRESSING SINCE EARLY FALL, HAS BEEN SLOW IN 
COMING.  NEVERTHELESS, WE HAVE HEARD FROM SOURCES WITHIN THE 
HOLY SEE THAT OUR REPEATED INTERVENTIONS -- RECENTLY 
REINFORCED BY OUR CANADIAN AND ARGENTINEAN DIPLOMATIC 
COLLEAGUES -- HAS GOTTEN THE HOLY SEE\'S ATTENTION AND LED TO 
MOVEMENT ON THE ISSUE.  SIGNIFICANTLY, THE POPE MADE TWO 
REFERENCES TO FAMINE IN AFRICA IN HIS ANNUAL ADDRESS TO THE 
DIPLOMATIC CORPS, REINFORCING THE FOCUS THE ISSUE IS NOW 
RECEDING.  THIS GROWING INTEREST WAS ALSO REFLECTED IN THE 
BROAD VATICAN PARTICIPATION AT AN EMBASSY-SPONSORED 
CONFERENCE JANUARY 27 ON BIOTECH IN AFRICA, WHICH WAS 
ATTENDED BY REPRESENTATIVES OF THE SECRETARIAT OF STATE, THE 
COUNCIL FOR JUSTICE AND PEACE, COR UNUM (RESPONSIBLE FOR 
HUMANITARIAN WORK), THE JESUIT DIRECTORS FOR AFRICA AND THE 
U.S., THE CARITAS CATHOLIC RELIEF AGENCY, THE SANT EGIDIO 
COMMUNITY, AND MEMBERS OF THE HOLY SEE DIPLOMATIC CORPS. 
EMBASSY LUSAKA\'S PRESSURE HAS ALSO BEEN HELPFUL IN RAISING 
THE HOLY SEE\'S APPRECIATION OF THE ISSUE, AND WE WOULD URGE 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  00402  02 OF 02  030859Z 
THAT THIS BE CONTINUED IN LIGHT OF THE NUNCIO\'S POSITIVE 
REPORT TO THE VATICAN ABOUT THE EMBASSY\'S EFFORTS TO ELICIT A 
MORE ACTIVE AND BALANCED POSITION.  EMBASSY VATICAN WILL 
CONTINUE TO ENGAGE THE HOLY SEE AND AFFILIATED AGENCIES IN 
ROME TO RESPOND TO THE CHALLENGE OF AFRICAN FAMINE AND TO 
ENSURE BROADER UNDERSTANDING OF THE SAFETY AND POTENTIAL 
BENEFITS OF BIOTECH FOODS. 
 
NICHOLSON 
 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
> 
 

 2003VATICA00402 - Classification: UNCLASSIFIED 

"
"5565","2/6/2003 14:15","03VATICAN483","Embassy Vatican","CONFIDENTIAL","03VATICAN5756","This record is a partial extract of the original cable. The full text of the original cable is not available.

","C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 01 OF 02 VATICAN 000483 
 
SIPDIS 
 
DEPT. FOR EUR/WE MENNUTI, S/ES/O, NEA 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 02/06/2013 
TAGS: IZ, PREL, PREL, PREL, PREL, VT, VTIZ, VTIZ, VTIZ 
SUBJECT: HOLY SEE REACTION TO SECRETARY\'S UNSC 
PRESENTATION; POPE TO MEET WITH TARIQ AZIZ FEBRUARY 14 
 
REF: VATICAN 5756 
 
CLASSIFIED BY: DCM BRENT HARDT.  REASONS 1.5 (B) AND (D) 
 
------- 
SUMMARY 
------- 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  00483  01 OF 02  070959Z 
 
1. (C) HOLY SEE OFFICIALS ARE STILL ASSESSING THE SECRETARY\'S 
UNSC PRESENTATION, AND HAVE INDICATED THEY WILL PROVIDE A 
CONSIDERED RESPONSE AFTER CONFERRING WITH THE FOREIGN 
MINISTER.  THEY SHARE THE U.S. VIEW THAT SADDAM IS A DANGER 
TO THE WORLD, AND HAVE NOW COME TO SEE THE MERITS OF HIS 
REMOVAL.  THE HOLY SEE CONTINUES TO OPPOSE WAR AS A MEANS TO 
ACHIEVE THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY\'S OBJECTIVES IN IRAQ, AND 
IS INTENSIFYING ITS DIPLOMATIC ACTIVITY TO HEAD OFF WAR. 
FOLLOWING WEEKS OF SPECULATION OF POSSIBLE HOLY SEE 
ENGAGEMENT WITH BAGHDAD, THE VATICAN CONFIRMED FEBRUARY 5 
THAT TARIQ AZIZ WOULD MEET WITH THE POPE FEBRUARY 14.  THE 
HOLY SEE\'S DEPUTY FOREIGN MINSTER TOLD US THE POPE WOULD URGE 
BAGHDAD TO COMPLY WITH UN RESOLUTIONS TO AVOID WAR, BUT WOULD 
ALSO EXPRESS SOLIDARITY WITH THE SUFFERING OF THE IRAQI 
PEOPLE.  GERMAN FOREIGN MINISTER JOSCHKA FISCHER WILL ALSO 
MEET WITH THE POPE FEBRUARY 7 TO DISCUSS IRAQ.  END SUMMARY 
 
--------------------------------------------- ------- 
RECOGNITION OF SADDAM\'S DANGER, BUT OPPOSED TO FORCE 
--------------------------------------------- ------- 
 
2. (C) IN EMBASSY\'S INITIAL CONTACTS WITH THE HOLY SEE 
FOLLOWING THE SECRETARY\'S PRESENTATION TO THE UNSC, VATICAN 
OFFICIALS HAVE INDICATED THAT THEY ARE STILL ASSESSING THE 
INFORMATION PROVIDED (WHICH FEW APPEARED TO HAVE WATCHED 
LIVE) AND WOULD OFFER AN OFFICIAL REACTION AFTER CONFERRING 
WITH FOREIGN MINISTER TAURAN.  HOWEVER, MIDDLE EAST COUNTRY 
DIRECTOR MONS. FRANCO COPPOLA TOLD POLOFF THAT THE VATICAN 
\"DOES NOT DISAGREE\" THAT SADDAM IS A DANGER BOTH TO HIS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  00483  01 OF 02  070959Z 
PEOPLE AND TO THE WORLD, AND SHOULD BE REMOVED.  THIS GOES 
FURTHER THAN PREVIOUS STATEMENTS WHICH HAVE RECOGNIZED 
SADDAM\'S DANGER, BUT DID NOT ACKNOWLEDGE THE IMPORTANCE OF 
HIS DEPARTURE.  COPPOLA ADDED THAT THE HOLY SEE STANDS BY ITS 
VIEW THAT WAR IS NOT THE BEST WAY TO EFFECT CHANGE IN BAGHDAD 
-- THOUGH HE DID NOT OFFER ANY ALTERNATIVE.  PRESSED ON THE 
SPECIFICS OF POWELL\'S PRESENTATION OF SADDAM\'S THREAT, HE 
SAID THE VATICAN DOES NOT HAVE A ROLE IN ASSESSING THE 
VERACITY OR MEANING OF THOSE FACTS -- BUT ASSUMES THE 
INSPECTORS WILL PLAY SUCH A ROLE.  PRESIDENT OF THE 
PONTIFICAL COUNCIL OF JUSTICE AND PEACE RENATO MARTINO TOLD 
VATICAN RADIO THAT THE PRESENTATION WAS \"NOT AN ADLAI 
STEVENSON MOMENT\" AND WOULD NOT CHANGE HIS VIEW ON THE 
NECESSITY OF WAR (THOUGH HE ACKNOWLEDGED TO THE REPORTED THAT 
HE HAD NOT SEEN THE PRESENTATION AND WAS BASING HIS COMMENTS 
ON TODAY\'S MEDIA REPORTS). 
 
----------------- 
AZIZ TO MEET POPE 
----------------- 
 
3.  (U) PRIOR TO THE SECRETARY\'S PRESENTATION, LE MONDE AND 
FIGARO HAD REPORTED THAT IRAQI FOREIGN MINISTER TARIQ AZIZ 
INFORMED REPORTERS HE WOULD BE MEETING WITH THE POPE FEBRUARY 
14.  THE HOLY SEE WAS CAUGHT OFF GUARD BY AZIZ\'S REVELATION, 
BUT SUBSEQUENTLY CONFIRMED THAT AZIZ WOULD MEET THE POPE AT 
AZIZ\'S REQUEST.  DEPUTY FOREIGN MINISTER PAROLIN TOLD DCM 
THAT THE POPE WOULD TELL IRAQ TO COLLABORATE \"WITHOUT 
RESERVATION\" WITH THE UN INSPECTORS TO ENSURE THE SUCCESS OF 
THE INSPECTION PROCESS AND AVOID A WAR.  AT THE SAME TIME, 
THE POPE WOULD ALSO LIKELY EXPRESS HIS SOLIDARITY FOR THE 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  00483  01 OF 02  070959Z 
SUFFERING OF THE IRAQI PEOPLE (HE HAD LAST MET WITH AZIZ IN 
1998 WHEN AZIZ WAS TOURING EUROPE SEEKING TO LIFT UN 
SANCTIONS) AND WOULD MAKE ANOTHER APPEAL FOR THE WORLD TO 
AVOID WAR.  MEDIA REACTION TO THE ANNOUNCEMENT HAS POINTED 
OUT THAT THE POPE\'S EFFORTS TO WORK WITH IRAQ WHEN HE HAD 
BEEN SEEKING TO VISIT ABRAHAM\'S BIRTHPLACE IN IRAQ DURING THE 
JUBILEE YEAR PROVED UNSUCCESSFUL.  AZIZ WILL ALSO LIKELY MEET 
WITH SECRETARY OF STATE SODANO AND FOREIGN MINISTER TAURAN, 
PER NORMAL VATICAN PROTOCOL.  ITALIAN PAPERS HAVE NOTED THAT 
CATHOLIC ACTIVIST FATHER JEAN-MARIE BENJAMIN, WHO HAS MADE 
DOCUMENTARIES ABOUT THE CONDITIONS OF THE IRAQI PEOPLE, 
PLAYED A KEY ROLE IN ARRANGING THE MEETING. 
 
---------------------------------- 
CATHOLIC MEDIA STILL NOT CONVINCED 
---------------------------------- 
 
4. (U) VATICAN-LINKED MEDIA GENERALLY REMAINED SKEPTICAL 
FOLLOWING THE SECRETARY\'S PRESENTATION.  ITALY\'S LEADING 
CATHOLIC DAILY, AVVENIRE, COMMENTED THAT THE SECRETARY\'S 
PRESENTATION DID NOT PROVIDE THE PROOF NEEDED TO END THE 
POLEMICS AND DISAGREEMENTS.  THEY ASSERTED THAT \"THOSE WHO 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
