DEPT. FOR EUR/WE MENNUTI, S/ES/O, NEA 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 02/06/2013 
TAGS: IZ, PREL, VT 
SUBJECT: HOLY SEE REACTION TO SECRETARY\'S UNSC 
PRESENTATION; POPE TO MEET WITH TARIQ AZIZ FEBRUARY 14 
 
WERE SKEPTICAL BEFORE YESTERDAY ABOUT THE NECESSITY OF 
DISARMING IRAQ REMAIN SO.\"  IN THE SAME PAPER, HOWEVER, 
ANOTHE ANALYST CRITICIZES THE PACIFIST DIRECTION WITHIN HE 
CHURCH AS LOOKING AT THE WORLD WITH BLINDERS ND IGNORING THE 
PROBLEMS OF IRAQ. 
 
------- 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  00483  02 OF 02  070959Z 
COMMENT 
------- 
 
5. (C)AS THE HOLY SEE INTENSIFIES ITS ENGAGEMENT TO AVER 
WAR, IT HAS BEGUN TO SHIFT ITS EMPHASIS FROM MOAL ARGUMENTS 
ABOUT THE MORALITY OF PREVENTIVE WAR(REFTEL) TO MORE 
PRAGMATIC STRATEGIC ARGUMENTS. COPPOLA CONFIRMED THIS SHIFT, 
NOTING THAT SECRETARY OF STATE SODANO\'S MOST RECENT REMARKS 
ON THE PRACTICAL IMPACT OF A WAR IN IRAQ -- THAT THE U.S. 
WOULD \"RISK IRRITATING A BILLION MUSLIMS\" --  REFLECTED THE 
VATICAN\'S DESIRE TO ENGAGE BEYOND THE MORAL ARGUMENTS TO THE 
PRACTICAL ARGUMENTS AGAINST WAR.  OTHER SENIOR VATICAN 
OFFICIALS HAVE STEPPED UP CRITICISM OF THE POSSIBILITY OF 
WAR, THOUGH SOME HAVE ALSO BEEN AT PAINS TO REITERATE THAT 
THE HOLY SEE IS NOT PACIFIST AND THAT IRAQ MUST RESPECT UN 
RESOLUTIONS.  THE POPE\'S MEETING WITH JOSCHKA FISCHER 
FEBRUARY 7 -- AT FISCHER\'S REQUEST -- REFLECTS THE DEEPENING 
ENGAGEMENT WE CAN EXPECT FROM THE HOLY SEE AS THE THREAT OF 
WAR INCREASES.  THE HOLY SEE HAS PREVIOUSLY INDICATED TO US 
THAT IT WAS KEEPING ITS ARROWS IN ITS QUIVER UNTIL ABSOLUTELY 
NEEDED; IT HAS APPARENTLY DECIDED THAT NOW IS THE TIME TO 
PULL THEM OUT.  EMBASSY WILL BE ACTIVELY ENGAGED IN THE WEEK 
AHEAD TO MAKE THE U.S. CASE ON IRAQ WITH THE VISITS OF 
CATHOLIC SCHOLAR MICHAEL NOVAK, WHO WILL MAKE PRESENTATIONS 
ON IRAQ AND JUST WAR, AND OF POLICY PLANNING STAFF MEMBER 
RICHARD ERDMAN, WHO WILL ADDRESS IRAQ ISSUES AND MEET WITH 
VATICAN OFFICIALS FEBRUARY 12.  DASD BRZEZINSKI WILL ALSO 
MEET WITH FM TAURAN FEBRUARY 7 TO REINFORCE THE U.S. CASE 
AGAINST IRAQ. 
NICHOLSON 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  00483  02 OF 02  070959Z 
 
