C O N F I D E N T I A L SECTION 03 OF 03 VATICAN 000683 
 
SIPDIS 
 
DEPT FOR EUR, EUR/WE-MENNUTI, NEA, S-KELLY AND GRAZE 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 02/19/2013 
TAGS: PREL, MOPS, PHUM, VT 
SUBJECT: SADDAM MEETING WITH CARDINAL ETCHEGARAY: VATICAN 
SEES \"LAST CHANCE FOR DIPLOMACY\" 
 
A PEACEMAKER, \"WORKING INTENSELY TO PREVENT THE OUTBREAK OF 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  00683  03 OF 03  200658Z 
CONFLICTS.\"  FOLLOWING ETCHEGARAY\'S MISSION, THE HOLY SEE IS 
GUARDEDLY OPTIMISTIC THAT DISARMAMENT CAN BE ACHIEVED 
PEACEFULLY, AS THEY CAME AWAY WITH A SENSE THAT IRAQ NOW 
UNDERSTANDS IT NEEDS TO BE GENUINELY, AND NOT BEGRUDGINGLY, 
COLLABORATIVE.  WHILE THE ETCHEGARAY VISIT WAS THE HOLY SEE\'S 
LAST, BEST SHOT AT CONVINCING SADDAM TO COMPLY, WE CAN EXPECT 
THE HOLY SEE TO CONTINUE TO PRESS ITS CASE PUBLICLY AND 
PRIVATELY THAT WAR SHOULD BE THE VERY LAST OPTION.  MOREOVER, 
THE HOLY SEE\'S OWN \"CONSTITUENT\" INTERESTS -- THE PHYSICAL 
SAFETY OF MILLIONS OF CHRISTIANS LIVING IN MUSLIM COUNTRIES 
BOTH DURING AND AFTER THE WAR -- WILL BE A FOREMOST CONCERN. 
AT THE SAME TIME, THE HOLY SEE FULLY SHARES OUR ASSESSMENT OF 
THE DANGERS PRESENTED BY INTERNATIONAL TERRORISM AND OF AN 
UNFETTERED SADDAM ARMED WITH WMD.  THEY ARE INCREASINGLY 
CONCERNED WITH THE GROWING PUBLIC PERCEPTION OF TRANSATLANTIC 
DISUNITY AND OF A SPLIT BETWEEN THE U.S. AND THE VATICAN, 
GIVEN THEIR BELIEF THAT WE ARE ALL SEEKING THE SAME GOAL OF 
IRAQI DISARMAMENT. 
 
9. (C) ACTION REQUEST:  THE POPE MET WITH UN SECRETARY 
GENERAL KOFI ANNAN FEBRUARY 19 AND WILL MEET PRIME MINSTER 
BLAIR FEBRUARY 22.  WE EXPECT THE POPE WILL CONTINUE TO 
PURSUE EVERY OPPORTUNITY TO PRESS FOR A RESOLUTION THAT 
AVOIDS WAR.  THERE HAS BEEN CONSIDERABLE MEDIA SPECULATION 
ABOUT A POTENTIAL PAPAL EMISSARY TO WASHINGTON REFLECTING THE 
HOLY SEE\'S DESIRE FOR GREATER CONTACT WITH WASHINGTON ON THE 
IRAQ ISSUE, BUT THE HOLY SEE HAS BEEN WARY OF BILATERALIZING 
THE CONFLICT BY SENDING EMISSARIES TO BAGHDAD AND WASHINGTON. 
 IN LIGHT OF THE HOLY SEE\'S DESIRE TO TONE DOWN PERCEPTIONS 
OF CONFLICT WITH THE UNITED STATES AND ITS DESIRE TO CONTINUE 
PUSHING FOR PEACEFUL SOLUTIONS, EMBASSY STRONGLY BELIEVES 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  00683  03 OF 03  200658Z 
THAT A MEETING BETWEEN A SENIOR USG OFFICIAL AND THE POPE 
WOULD SERVE TO REINFORCE OUR SHARED OBJECTIVE OF PEACEFUL 
IRAQI DISARMAMENT WHILE HELPING OVERCOME PERCEPTIONS OF 
DIVISION BETWEEN THE U.S. AND THE HOLY SEE AT THIS CRITICAL 
TIME. 
NICHOLSON 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
> 
 

