DEPT. FOR T U/S BOLTON, EUR, EUR/WE-MENNUTI 
 
E.O. 12958: DECL: 04/09/2013 
TAGS: PREL, IZ, VT 
SUBJECT: VATICAN LOOKING FORWARD: U/S BOLTON REVIEWS 
POST-WAR IRAQ AND GLOBAL WMD THREATS WITH HOLY SEE FM AND 
SENIOR OFFICIALS 
 
DISSIPATE.  BOLTON RESPONDED THAT THE UN WOULD, AS THE 
PRESIDENT HAD STATED, PLAY A VITAL ROLE.  HOWEVER, IT WAS 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  01570  02 OF 03  131014Z 
IMPORTANT NOT TO GET BOGGED DOWN IN THEOLOGICAL DEBATES ABOUT 
THE NATURE OF THIS ROLE.  THE ISSUE AT HAND WAS NOT WHETHER 
THE U.S. OR UN WOULD CONTROL IRAQ, BUT HOW SOON CONTROL COULD 
BE TURNED OVER TO A LEGITIMATE IRAQI AUTHORITY.  IN THE 
MEANTIME, IT WAS VITAL TO CONCENTRATE ON RESOLVING PRACTICAL 
ISSUES TO PROVIDE RELIEF TO THE IRAQI PEOPLE.  IN THIS, THE 
UN WOULD PLAY A CENTRAL ROLE, BOLTON ASSURED HIS 
INTERLOCUTORS.  TAURAN CONCURRED THAT THIS WAS VITAL, AND 
OBSERVED THAT THE IRAQI PEOPLE WERE \"INTELLECTUALLY 
WELL-EQUIPPED,\" WHICH WOULD FACILITATE AN EARLY TRANSITION TO 
IRAQI AUTHORITY.  TO REINFORCE THIS POINT HE QUOTED AN ARAB 
APHORISM THAT \"BOOKS WERE WRITTEN IN CAIRO, PRINTED IN 
LEBANON, AND READ IN BAGHDAD.\"  BOLTON AFFIRMED THAT THE U.S. 
HAD NO DESIRE FOR A LONG OCCUPATION.  OUR GOALS, HE ADDED, 
WERE TO FIND AND DESTROY WMD, PRESERVE EXTERNAL SECURITY IN 
THE SHORT-TERM, AND TURN AUTHORITY OVER TO LEGITIMATE, 
DEMOCRATIC IRAQI AUTHORITY AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.  RUINI ALSO 
WELCOMED THIS COMMITMENT, OBSERVING \"IF IT IS POSSIBLE TO 
TURN AUTHORITY OVER TO IRAQI\'S IN A SHORT TIME, THAT WOULD BE 
IDEAL.\" 
 
---------------------- 
THE BROADER WMD THREAT 
---------------------- 
 
5. (C) WITH ALL OF HIS VATICAN INTERLOCUTORS, BOLTON REVIEWED 
THE BROADER WMD THREAT, STRESSING THAT WEAPONS OF MASS 
DESTRUCTION ARE NOT MILITARY WEAPONS, AND CAN ONLY BE USED TO 
KILL CIVILIANS, AS SADDAM HUSSEIN HAD WITH HIS OWN PEOPLE. 
ALL VATICAN INTERLOCUTORS EXPRESSED CONCERN WITH WHAT HAPPENS 
NEXT, NOTING FEARS THAT THE WAR ON IRAQ COULD BE FOLLOWED 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 03        VATICA  01570  02 OF 03  131014Z 
WITH OTHER ACTIONS AGAINST IRAN, SYRIA, OR NORTH KOREA. 
BOLTON MADE CLEAR THAT IRAQ WAS NOT A MODEL FOR NORTH KOREA, 
IRAN OR SYRIA, AND THAT THERE IS NO \'COOKIE CUTTER\' APPROACH 
TO RESOLVING THESE ISSUES.  HE POINTED OUT THAT WE WERE 
ACTIVELY PURSUING DIPLOMATIC INITIATIVES IN ALL OF THESE 
CASES, AND THAT WE HOPED THESE COUNTRIES WOULD DRAW THE RIGHT 
LESSON FROM THE IRAQ EXAMPLE:  THAT IT WAS NOT WORTH IT FOR 
THEM TO CONTINUE PURSUING WMD.  ALL THREE VATICAN OFFICIALS 
EXPRESSED THEIR BELIEF THAT THE U.S. SHOULD SEEK TO WORK WITH 
OTHER COUNTRIES IN A MULTILATERAL EFFORT TO DEAL WITH THESE 
THREATS TO THE EXTENT POSSIBLE. 
 
6.  (C) TURNING TO SPECIFIC COUNTRIES, TAURAN FOCUSED FIRST 
ON NORTH KOREA, ABOUT WHICH HE ACKNOWLEDGED THE HOLY SEE HAD 
LIMITED UNDERSTANDING.  BOLTON REVIEWED THE BACKGROUND TO THE 
DISCOVERY OF THE NORTH KOREAN PROGRAM AND OUR EFFORTS TO 
PERSUADE NORTH KOREA TO ABANDON ITS PROGRAM.  HE EMPHASIZED 
THAT WE WERE ACTIVELY TRYING TO ENGAGE CHINA AND RUSSIA TO 
BECOME MORE INVOLVED, WHILE WORKING WITH JAPAN AND SOUTH 
KOREA.  HE POINTED OUT THE HIGH STAKES INVOLVED, GIVEN 
SUPPORT IN JAPAN FOR A NUCLEAR PROGRAM TO COUNTER A NORTH 
KOREAN THREAT AND THE SUBSEQUENT POTENTIAL FOR AN ASIAN ARMS 
RACE BETWEEN JAPAN AND CHINA. 
 
7.  (C) ON IRAN, BOLTON OUTLINED LONG-STANDING CONCERNS THAT 
IRAN WAS PURSUING A COMPLETE ENRICHMENT PROGRAM THAT WOULD 
GIVE THE IRANIANS THE CAPACITY TO MAKE NUCLEAR WEAPONS.  HE 
REVIEWED OUR EFFORTS TO ENCOURAGE RUSSIA TO CUT OFF 
ASSISTANCE, AND THE FINDINGS FROM THE RECENT VISIT OF THE 
IAEA INSPECTORS, WHICH SURPRISED MANY IN THE IAEA.  TAURAN 
ASKED WHETHER WE FOUND RUSSIA TO BE A RELIABLE INTERLOCUTOR, 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
PAGE 04        VATICA  01570  02 OF 03  131014Z 
NOTING THAT THE HOLY SEE FOUND THEY HAD GOOD RESULTS FROM TOP 
RUSSIAN LEADERSHIP, BUT THAT THERE WAS NO FOLLOW THROUGH FROM 
OTHER PARTS OF THE GOVERNMENT.  TAURAN ALSO EMPHASIZED THAT 
THE HOLY SEE REGARDED IRAN AS \"A KEY COUNTRY\" IN THE MIDDLE 
EAST AND URGED THAT WE SUPPORT ANY SIGNS OF A \"DEMOCRATIC 
OPENING.\"  BOLTON SAID WE REMAINED DEEPLY CONCERNED BY RECENT 
SYRIAN ACTIONS AS WELL AS SYRIA\'S CONTINUED PURSUIT OF WMD. 
TAURAN SAID HE BELIEVED THE BRITISH COULD PLAY AN IMPORTANT 
ROLE WITH SYRIA, WHILE BOLTON NOTED THAT THE FRENCH COULD 
ALSO BE CONSTRUCTIVE. 
 
---------------------------------------- 
REINVIGORATING MIDDLE EAST PEACE PROCESS 
---------------------------------------- 
 
8. (C) BOLTON ASSURED TAURAN AND THE OTHER OFFICIALS THAT THE 
U.S. WAS COMMITTED TO REINVIGORATING OUR EFFORTS TO RESOLVE 
THE ISRAELI-PALESTINIAN CRISIS ONCE THE IRAQ CRISIS WAS 
BEHIND US.  HE ADDED THAT THE PRESIDENT WOULD DEEPEN HIS 
ALREADY CONSIDERABLE INVOLVEMENT ONCE THE NEW PALESTINIAN 
PRIME MINISTER WAS IN PLACE AND HAD AUTHORITY TO ACT 
EFFECTIVELY.  TAURAN WELCOMED THIS COMMITMENT, COMMENTING 
THAT THE ISRAELI-PALESTINIAN DISPUTE WAS \"THE MOTHER OF ALL 
 
                       CONFIDENTIAL 
 
                           CONFIDENTIAL     PTQ2800 
 
PAGE 01        VATICA  01570  03 OF 03  131014Z 
ACTION EUR-00 
 
INFO  LOG-00   NP-00    AMAD-00  CIAE-00  INL-00   PERC-00  DS-00 
      VC-00    TEDE-00  INR-00   IO-00    VCE-00   MED-07   NEA-00 
      NSAE-00  DHS-00   PM-00    IRM-00   SSO-00   SS-00    T-00 
      EPAE-00  PMB-00   DSCC-00  PRM-00   G-00     SAS-00   SWCI-00 
