OPPORTUNITY FOR THE HOLY SEE TO REINFORCE ITS GLOBAL REACH 
                       UNCLASSIFIED 
 
PAGE 02        VATICA  01694  02 OF 02  221343Z 
AND CONCERN, AND TO CALL INTERNATIONAL PUBLIC ATTENTION TO 
AREAS THE VATICAN BELIEVES REQUIRE THE MOST URGENT 
ATTENTION.  THE ABSENCE OF DIRECT CRITICISM ABOUT THE 
SITUATION IN IRAQ AND THE CLEAR EFFORT TO BROADEN GLOBAL 
FOCUS BEYOND IRAQ REINFORCES THE MESSAGE CONVEYED TO U/S 
BOLTON RECENTLY (REFTEL) OF A VATICAN SEEKING TO MOVE 
BEYOND RECENT TENSIONS OVER IRAQ AND REINVIGORATE 
COOPERATION TO ADDRESS OTHER TROUBLE SPOTS AND LONG-RANGE 
PRIORITIES.  THROUGHOUT THIS PHYSICALLY DEMANDING PERIOD, 
THE POPE APPEARED TO BE IN GOOD PHYSICAL FORM, FREQUENTLY 
RAISING HIS VOICE FOR EMPHASIS AND EXTEMPORIZING IN 
RESPONSE TO ACTIONS FROM THE FAITHFUL.  THE POPE\'S 
PARTICIPATION WAS FACILITATED THIS YEAR WITH A NEW MOBILE 
PAPAL THRONE THAT CAN BE RAISED AND LOWERED ACCORDING TO 
LITURGICAL REQUIREMENTS.  END COMMENT. 
 
